The last bunch of wildflowers,
along the fence,  
    are trembling
          under the sun
as it shimmers over the hills.
Their yellow petal arms reach out
in good cheer,  
apologizing,
  
Such beauty left behind
but never retained,
     all  
fleeting, free.


- William Carlos Williams
